<font color="#FF0000">COMMENTS TO DOC</font><br>
<tt>Fri Sep 12 21:46:10 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc,<br><br>
We must acknowledge that wanting to stay alive and having to work at staying alive creates two completely different points of view completely valid within the context of the individual who experienced either. If you think about that, some of the disconnects on this site are directly attributable to that difference alone. It is also true that irreconcilable differences are spawned by this which we must accept as a fact of life and move ahead.<br><br>
Working at staying alive in the Vietnam War was a second to second existance whose only certainty was uncertainty. I cannot think that any 'Nam Vet who totally escaped that experience. We differ only in the manner in which we handled and processed the experience. It is only natural that those with similar experiences form connectiuons that are supportive and protective. This is the Hyena Pack, which you have labled it. Although I may not agree with another 'Nam Vet's opinions, and I may so state, as I have done from time to time, the connection still exists. It is a connection which transcends time and space. It does not mean that any of us has abandoned our personal ethics, principles, values, or what have you. It simply means that we share a common experience, and are supportive of each other in that regard.<br><br>
Tom does a very good job at nipping at the heels of the pack. It is a necessity that we all respect. We have all assumed roles here, so to speak, and I dare say that if you look at any unit back in 'Nam, there will be similarities to what is seen here. There were guys in my units very much like Cook, and SW, and M24, and Tom, and me, too. This is a fact of life. I dare say that we interacted in ways you can see here, too.<br><br>
This is a looking glass into the Vietnam experience. Unlike Alice, the catepillar, and the two sided mushroom, there is a diversity here that is to be savored, respected, and enjoyed.<br><br>
If you listen to anyone here, listen to SW. <br><br>
   
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


